com.github.upthewaterspout.fates.core.threading.instrument

Class ExecutionEventSingleton

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.upthewaterspout.fates.core.threading.instrument.ExecutionEventSingleton

  • public class ExecutionEventSingleton
extends java.lang.Object
    Static methods that should be called from instrumented bytecode to control the execution of code. All instrumentation of bytecode ends up creating calls to static methods in this class. This class is responsible for taking those calls and passing them to a single, installed ExecutionEventListener which is installed by setListener(ExecutionEventListener) This class will atomically decorate the passed in listener with a NonReentrantExecutionEventListener
